#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:4
msgid "history - show and manipulate command history"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:7
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:9
msgid ""
"history [search] [--show-time] [--case-sensitive]\n"
"                 [--exact | --prefix | --contains] [--max N] [--null] [--"
"reverse]\n"
"                 [SEARCH_STRING ...]\n"
"history delete [--case-sensitive]\n"
"               [--exact | --prefix | --contains] SEARCH_STRING ...\n"
"history merge\n"
"history save\n"
"history clear\n"
"history clear-session"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:22
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:24
msgid ""
"``history`` is used to search, delete, and otherwise manipulate the :ref:"
"`history of interactive commands <history-search>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:26
msgid "The following operations (sub-commands) are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:28
msgid "**search**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:29
msgid ""
"Returns history items matching the search string. If no search string is "
"provided it returns all history items. This is the default operation if no "
"other operation is specified. You only have to explicitly say ``history "
"search`` if you wish to search for one of the subcommands. The ``--"
"contains`` search option will be used if you don't specify a different "
"search option. Entries are ordered newest to oldest unless you use the ``--"
"reverse`` flag. If stdout is attached to a tty the output will be piped "
"through your pager by the history function. The history builtin simply "
"writes the results to stdout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:31
msgid "**delete**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:32
msgid ""
"Deletes history items. The ``--contains`` search option will be used if you "
"don't specify a different search option. If you don't specify ``--exact`` a "
"prompt will be displayed before any items are deleted asking you which "
"entries are to be deleted. You can enter the word \"all\" to delete all "
"matching entries. You can enter a single ID (the number in square brackets) "
"to delete just that single entry. You can enter more than one ID, or an ID "
"range separated by a space to delete multiple entries. Just press [enter] to "
"not delete anything. Note that the interactive delete behavior is a feature "
"of the history function. The history builtin only supports ``--exact --case-"
"sensitive`` deletion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:34
msgid "**merge**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:35
msgid ""
"Immediately incorporates history changes from other sessions. Ordinarily "
"``fish`` ignores history changes from sessions started after the current "
"one. This command applies those changes immediately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:37
msgid "**save**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:38
msgid ""
"Immediately writes all changes to the history file. The shell automatically "
"saves the history file; this option is provided for internal use and should "
"not normally need to be used by the user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:40
msgid "**clear**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:41
msgid ""
"Clears the history file. A prompt is displayed before the history is erased "
"asking you to confirm you really want to clear all history unless ``builtin "
"history`` is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:43
msgid "**clear-session**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:44
msgid ""
"Clears the history file from all activity of the current session. Note: If "
"``history merge`` or ``builtin history merge`` is run in a session, only the "
"history after this will be erased."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:46
msgid "The following options are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:48
msgid ""
"These flags can appear before or immediately after one of the sub-commands "
"listed above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:50
msgid "**-C** or **--case-sensitive**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:51
msgid ""
"Does a case-sensitive search. The default is case-insensitive. Note that "
"prior to fish 2.4.0 the default was case-sensitive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:53
msgid "**-c** or **--contains**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:54
msgid ""
"Searches items in the history that contain the specified text string. This "
"is the default for the **--search** flag. This is not currently supported by "
"the **delete** subcommand."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:56
msgid "**-e** or **--exact**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:57
msgid ""
"Searches or deletes items in the history that exactly match the specified "
"text string. This is the default for the **delete** subcommand. Note that "
"the match is case-insensitive by default. If you really want an exact match, "
"including letter case, you must use the **-C** or **--case-sensitive** flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:59
msgid "**-p** or **--prefix**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:60
msgid ""
"Searches items in the history that begin with the specified text string. "
"This is not currently supported by the **delete** subcommand."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:62
msgid "**-t** or **--show-time**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:63
msgid ""
"Prepends each history entry with the date and time the entry was recorded. "
"By default it uses the strftime format ``# %c%n``. You can specify another "
"format; e.g., ``--show-time=\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S \"`` or ``--show-"
"time=\"%a%I%p\"``. The short option, **-t**, doesn't accept a strftime "
"format string; it only uses the default format. Any strftime format is "
"allowed, including ``%s`` to get the raw UNIX seconds since the epoch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:65
msgid "**-z** or **--null**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:66
msgid ""
"Causes history entries written by the search operations to be terminated by "
"a NUL character rather than a newline. This allows the output to be "
"processed by ``read -z`` to correctly handle multiline history entries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:68
msgid "**-**\\*NUMBER* **-n** *NUMBER* or **--max** *NUMBER*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:69
msgid ""
"Limits the matched history items to the first *NUMBER* matching entries. "
"This is only valid for ``history search``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:71
msgid "**-R** or **--reverse**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:72
msgid ""
"Causes the history search results to be ordered oldest to newest. Which is "
"the order used by most shells. The default is newest to oldest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:74
msgid "**-h** or **--help**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:75
msgid "Displays help for this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:78
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:84
msgid ""
"history clear\n"
"# Deletes all history items\n"
"\n"
"history search --contains \"foo\"\n"
"# Outputs a list of all previous commands containing the string \"foo\".\n"
"\n"
"history delete --prefix \"foo\"\n"
"# Interactively deletes commands which start with \"foo\" from the history.\n"
"# You can select more than one entry by entering their IDs separated by a "
"space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:96
msgid "Customizing the name of the history file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:98
msgid ""
"By default interactive commands are logged to ``$XDG_DATA_HOME/fish/"
"fish_history`` (typically ``~/.local/share/fish/fish_history``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:100
msgid ""
"You can set the ``fish_history`` variable to another name for the current "
"shell session. The default value (when the variable is unset) is ``fish`` "
"which corresponds to ``$XDG_DATA_HOME/fish/fish_history``. If you set it to "
"e.g. ``fun``, the history would be written to ``$XDG_DATA_HOME/fish/"
"fun_history``. An empty string means history will not be stored at all. This "
"is similar to the private session features in web browsers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:102
msgid ""
"You can change ``fish_history`` at any time (by using ``set -x fish_history "
"\"session_name\"``) and it will take effect right away. If you set it to "
"``\"default\"``, it will use the default session name (which is "
"``\"fish\"``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:104
msgid ""
"Other shells such as bash and zsh use a variable named ``HISTFILE`` for a "
"similar purpose. Fish uses a different name to avoid conflicts and signal "
"that the behavior is different (session name instead of a file path). Also, "
"if you set the var to anything other than ``fish`` or ``default`` it will "
"inhibit importing the bash history. That's because the most common use case "
"for this feature is to avoid leaking private or sensitive history when "
"giving a presentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:107
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:109
msgid ""
"If you specify both **--prefix** and **--contains** the last flag seen is "
"used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/history.rst:111
msgid ""
"Note that for backwards compatibility each subcommand can also be specified "
"as a long option. For example, rather than ``history search`` you can type "
"``history --search``. Those long options are deprecated and will be removed "
"in a future release."
msgstr ""
